# tuple-monoid

_tupleConcat hot path — 100k iterations of (1,2) ++ (3,4).

Note: interp (tryFoldCounterLoop) and JVM (JvmGen constant hoisting +
HotSpot folding) both legitimately collapse this to O(1), reporting near-zero
times.  The JS number (no such optimization) is the actionable gap.

```scalascript
def workload(): (Int, Int, Int, Int) =
  var i = 0
  var last = (0, 0, 0, 0)
  while i < 100000 do
    last = (1, 2) ++ (3, 4)
    i = i + 1
  last
```
